THE ruling Chama cha Mapinduzi (CCM), National Chairman John Magufuli has tasked leaders of his party to track ongoing development project in their localities. Addressing a special meeting that brought together CCM top leaders from all regions and districts at Julius Nyerere Conference Centre (JNCC) in Dar es Salaam on Friday, he said government officials should be aware that the ruling party has mandate to do so. The President said his government is executing various development projects, mostly funded by wananchi through their taxes and reminded the partyâ€™s leaders from across the country to make a follow up.